sql:
SELECT AVG(log_all) AS average_expression
FROM expression_data
WHERE gene_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(gene_id) AS gene_count
FROM gene_pathway_mapping
WHERE pathway_id = 1;

SELECT MAX(log_all) AS max_expression_level
FROM expression_data
WHERE gene_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "Highest expression levels" refers to the greatest values in the `log_all` column;
- The top three genes per pathway and experiment signify the ones with the highest expression levels when compared to all others within the same pathway and experiment combination;
- Prominent expression is a qualitative term meaning high expression levels.
